- myVariable = "test"
  is actually
  var myVariable;
  myVariable = "test";
- to make a global variable
      exports = this
      exports.myVariable = "foo-bar"
  in the root context, _this_ is the global object
- function () {
    }
    becomes
  func = -> "bar"

  the last expression in a function is implicitly returned

  function arguments go before arrow
    func = (a,b) -> (a*b)

